HPCC Random Access Benchmarks
===============================

Compiling
----------

1. To compile the vanilla, unoptimized version
   make -f Makefile.nopt

2. To compile the optimized version:
   make -f Makefile.opt

3. To compile the hybrid MPI/OpenMP version:
   make -f Makefile.mpiomp

Running
------------------

1. To run the MPI code

mpirun -np #procs executable

2. To run the hybrid MPI/OpenMP code

Set the OMP_NUM_THREADS environment variable to the number of threads

e.g. $export OMP_NUM_THREADS=4

mpirun -np #procs executable

#procs is the number of processes



Cleaning up
----------- 

1. To clean only the object files

make -f Makefile.nopt clean  #specify any Makefile

2. To clean object files and executables

make -f Makefile.nopt cleanall #specify any Makefile